  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "TokenVesting and TokenTimelock allow for a single beneficiary each. It would be nice to have a single contract that could be used to vest multiple accounts.\r\n\r\nIs there a reason this wasn't done in the already built Zeppelin contracts?\r\nAre there any example crowdsales that offer this functionality that may be worth reading?\r\n\r\nOne way to use the current TokenVesting contract is to create a new contract for each account that needs to be vested. This is a little gas intensive and therefore expensive, but often this will be a minor issue in the case of ICOs. Is this the recommended way to use OpenZeppelin TokenVesting?\r\n\r\n ðŸ“ˆ This is a feature request.\r\n",
