    "body": "Not sure why the decision was made, but it was probably due to \"least concerns\".\r\n\r\nI expect you could compose the TokenVesting contract with a SplitPayment style contract to accomplish the same goal. The only difference is that the SplitPayment contract would have to \"pull\" the ether/tokens from the vesting contract before allowing beneficiaries to withdraw.\r\n\r\nAny ideas on how that could be structured, without making backwards-incompatible changes to the existing TokenVesting/TokenTimelock contracts?",
